# Task: Nested Logic Test (Depth 3)
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: checkNested(self, x0: int, x1: int, x2: int) -> bool

# Objective:
This is a test of structural nesting. Return True ONLY if all the following conditions are met:
1. x0 is greater than 0
2. x1 is greater than 0
3. x2 is greater than 0

Each condition must be checked inside the previous one (nested if statements).
lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "check_nested")
  (signature ( (x0 int) (x1 int) (x2 int) ) bool)
  (constraints
    (constraint "All input values must be greater than 0.")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Return True if all conditions are met: x0 > 0, x1 > 0, and x2 > 0.")
    (rule "Check each condition sequentially within the function.")
    (return "True only if all conditions are satisfied.")
  )
)
